Package: libsigar1.6-java
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, liblog4j1.2-java, junit,
         libsigar1.6 (= 1.6.4-1)
Description: System Information Gatherer And Reporter - Java bindings
 The Sigar API provides a portable interface for gathering system information
 such as:
 .
    System memory, swap, cpu, load average, uptime, logins
    Per-process memory, cpu, credential info, state, arguments, environment,
    open files File system detection and metrics
    Network interface detection, configuration info and metrics
    TCP and UDP connection tables
    Network route table
 .
 This information is available in most operating systems, but each OS has their
 own way(s) providing it. SIGAR provides developers with one API to access
 this information regardless of the underlying platform.
 .
 This package provides the Java bindings for SIGAR.

